physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Normal height and normal external genitalia apart from bilateral nonpalpable testes. S1 underwent laparoscopy at 7 years; S2 underwent laparotomy at 4 years. Both siblings had nonpalpable testes with associated findings of midline hypoplastic uterus.

physical_examinations.vital_signs: Serum AMH concentrations: S1 (10 yr) 327 pmol/liter, S2 (7 yr) 36 pmol/liter, S3 (5 yr) 380 pmol/liter.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Low serum AMH concentration in S2 unexpectedly; S1 and S3 concentrations are normal.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Serum T responded well to hCG in S1 and S2.
